      "text": [
        ": \"إِذَا قَتَلَ اَلْعَبْدُ اَلْحُرَّ فَلِأَهْلِ اَلْمَقْتُولِ إِنْ شَاءُوا قَتَلُوا وَ إِنْ شَاءُوا اِسْتَعْبَدُوا\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5263 - Yahya ibn Abi Al-'Ala narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) who said:\n\"If a slave kills a free man, the family of the murdered person has the choice: if they wish, they may kill him, and if they wish, they may enslave him.\""
